  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f11a3a413f1cd1b9c20fc387b12ad9",
        "content": [
          "## Table usage\r\n",
          "MI/MO new mirror or detach use bi_output_vg_copy_mimo.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "## Key Concepts\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- **ParentCID / RealCID (in parentcid)**: The Popular Investor's customer ID. In copy_mimo, ParentCID is the PI being copied and RealCID is the copier.\r\n",
          "- **MirrorID**: A unique copy relationship between a copier and a PI.\r\n",
          "- **NewMirror**: Dollar amount when a copier starts copying a PI.\r\n",
          "- **CloseMirror**: Dollar amount when a copier stops copying a PI.\r\n",
          "- **MoneyInMirror (MI)**: Dollar amount added to an existing copy.\r\n",
          "- **MoneyOutMirror (MO)**: Dollar amount removed from an existing copy without closing it.\r\n",
          "- **NetMI**: MI minus MO for a given day.\r\n",
          "- **CopyAUC**: Total equity (assets under copy) that copiers have allocated to a PI.\r\n",
          "- **NumOfCopiers**: Count of active copiers for a PI on a given date.\r\n",
          "- **GuruStatus / GuruStatusID**: PI program tier (Cadet, Rising Star, Champion, Elite). GuruStatusID >= 2 means the user is a PI.\r\n",
          "- **IsPI**: Flag (1/0) indicating PI status.\r\n",
          "- **CopyType**: Whether the entity is a PI, SmartPortfolio, or removed from PI status.\r\n",
          "- **IsDetachMirror**: When a copier detaches positions from a copy — positions become manual trades.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "## Common Query Patterns\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- When asked about PI-level metrics (AUC, copiers, performance), use parentcid alone.\r\n",
          "- When asked about copy actions (who copied whom, money flows), use copy_mimo alone or joined to parentcid for PI attributes.\r\n",
          "- Always filter on DateID or date range to avoid scanning the full history.\r\n",
          "- Use IsLastDayMonth = 1, IsLastDayWeek = 1 etc. from parentcid for period-end snapshots.\r\n",
          "- For \"current\" or \"latest\" data, use MAX(DateID) as the filter.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "## Date Handling\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- When the user mentions a day/month/quarter without specifying a year (e.g., \"in February\"), assume the most recent occurrence of that month relative to today's date.\r\n",
          "- Always confirm the date if ambiguous."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "join_specs": [
      {
        "id": "01f11a39c21819afa00006c16daf2418",
        "left": {
          "identifier": "main.bi_output.bi_output_vg_copy_mimo",
          "alias": "bi_output_vg_copy_mimo"
        },
        "right": {
          "identifier": "main.bi_output.bi_output_vg_parentcid",
          "alias": "bi_output_vg_parentcid"
        },
        "sql": [
          "bi_output_vg_parentcid.RealCID = bi_output_vg_copy_mimo.ParentCID AND bi_output_vg_parentcid.DateID = bi_output_vg_copy_mimo.DateID",
          "--rt=FROM_RELATIONSHIP_TYPE_MANY_TO_ONE--"
        ],
        "instruction": [
          "## Joins\n",
          "\n",
          "Always join these tables using BOTH keys:\n",
          "- bi_output_vg_parentcid.RealCID = bi_output_vg_copy_mimo.ParentCID\n",
          "- bi_output_vg_parentcid.DateID = bi_output_vg_copy_mimo.DateID\n",
          "\n",
          "The parentcid table is the PI-level dimension (one row per PI per day).\n",
          "The copy_mimo table is the copier-level fact (many rows per PI per day)."
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
